Colombian Stocks: Bancolombia Falls; Coltejer, Fabricato Rise

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-06-16T16:00:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/colombian-stocks-bancolombia-falls-coltejer-fabricato-rise.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:40 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.3 percent to 14,070.3, while the
Colcap Index advanced 0.1 percent to 1,703.65.  Bancolombia SA (BCOLO)  , Colombia’s biggest bank, fell
0.8 percent to 29,180 pesos after Chief Executive Officer Carlos
Raul Yepes said in an interview with Bloomberg News yesterday
that the bank may sell about $500 million of bonds in the third
quarter and could issue shares to fund a potential acquisition
in Central America or the Caribbean.  Textile makers rose after Reuters reported that the U.S.
Chamber of Commerce said yesterday the Obama administration and
congressional negotiators are close to a deal on a retraining
program that has held up votes on trade agreements with
Colombia,  South Korea  and Panama.  Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)  , the Medellin-based clothing maker
and exporter, rose 2.4 percent to 87 centavos, a one-month high.  Fabricato SA (FABRI CB),  Colombia ’s largest textile maker,
gained 1.7 percent to 61 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  